{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐλέγχω</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.424, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> ἐλέγξω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1043, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἤλεγξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.522, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> ἐλεγχθήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 2.4.10, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.7.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἠλέγχθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator [same place], 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 458a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἐλήλεγμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 805c: _3rd.pers._ _sing._ ἐλήλεγκται Antipho [prev. cited] (ἐξ-ηλεγμένοι\">Refs</a>] is <i>falsa lectio</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 6.44)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>pluperfect</i> ἐξ-ελήλεγκτο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 32.27 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>disgrace, put to shame</b>, μῦθον ἐ. <b>treat</b> a speech <b>with contempt</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.522 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. τινά <b>put</b> one <b>to shame</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.424.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —This usage is only _Epic dialect_ <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>cross-examine, question</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.115, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 18d, etc.; μὴ 'λεγχε τὸν πονοῦντα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 919; φύλαξ ἐλέγχων φύλακα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 260; τί ταῦτ᾽ ἄλλως ἐλέγχει; [prev. author] “OT” 333, compare 783; ἔλεγχ᾽, ἐλέγχου 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 857; ἐ. τινὰ περί τινος [prev. author] “Pl.” 574; ἕνεκά τινος 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 207.10; τὰς ἀρχὰς βασάνοις χρώμενοι ἐλεγχόντων 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 946c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, <b>accuse</b> one of doing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 1058 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be convicted</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.24, 117; ἐλεγχόμενοι εἴ τι περιγένοιτο τῶν χρημάτων 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 35.36, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 331c, 331d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, ἐλεγχθεὶς διαφθείρας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 2.3.9, compare 2.4.10; ἐλεγχθήσεται γελοῖος ὤν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.7.2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>test, bring to the proof</b>, ἀνδρῶν ἀρετὰν παγκρατὴς ἐλέγχει ἀλάθεια [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus “fragment” 10.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρᾶγμ᾽ ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1351 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (<i>passive</i>, τὸ πρᾶγμ᾽ ἐλεγχθέν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 485); λόγον 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 242b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tht.” 161e): with subject. clause, ἐ. τινά, εἰ.., 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 851, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1232. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>prove</b>, τοῦτο ἐ. ὡς.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 273b, compare “Sph.” 256c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>bring convincing proof</b>, ὡς ἡ ἀνάγκη ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.22 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αὐτὸ τὸ ἔργον ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.86; περί τινος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>refute, confute</b>, τινά or τι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 470c, +others, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 28.2, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 162a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χρυσὸς κληῖδας ἐλέγχει <b>proves that</b> they <b>avail not,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anthologia Graeca 5.216 (Paul. Sil.). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.4.b</b></Level4> <b>put right, correct, prove by a reductio ad impossibile</b>, ὅσα ἔστιν ἀποδεῖξαι, ἔστι καὶ ἐλέγξαι τὸν θέμενον τὴν ἀντίφασιν τοῦ ἀληθοῦς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Sophistici Elenchi” 170a24 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; παράδοξα ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “EN” 1146a23. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>get the better of</b>, στρατιὰν ὠκύτατι ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 11.49, compare 2nd c.AD: Dionysius Periegeta 750, 4th c.AD: Himerius Sophista “Orationes” 1.16. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <b>expose</b>, τινὰ ληροῦντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 171d, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.7.2, 2nd c.AD: Marcus Antoninus Imperator 1.17 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>betray</b> a weakness, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 222. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.7</b></Level3> <b>decide</b> a dispute, ἀνὰ μέσον τῶν δύο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Gen.31.37. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G1651","accentedUnicode":"ἐλέγχω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0483","matchingForm":"ἀντιλέγω","stepTransliteration":"antilegō","gloss":"to dispute","_zh_tw_Gloss":"反對","_es_Gloss":"disputar","_zh_Gloss":"反对"},{"strongNumber":"G0557","matchingForm":"ἀπελεγμός","stepTransliteration":"apelegmos","gloss":"discredit","_zh_tw_Gloss":"藐視","_es_Gloss":"descrédito","_zh_Gloss":"藐视"},{"strongNumber":"G1246","matchingForm":"διακατελέγχομαι","stepTransliteration":"diakatelenchomai","gloss":"to refute","_zh_tw_Gloss":"駁倒","_es_Gloss":"refutar ","_zh_Gloss":"驳倒"},{"strongNumber":"G1256","matchingForm":"διαλέγω","stepTransliteration":"dialegō","gloss":"to dispute","_zh_tw_Gloss":"辯論","_es_Gloss":"disputar ","_zh_Gloss":"辩论"},{"strongNumber":"G1649","matchingForm":"ἔλεγξις","stepTransliteration":"elegxis","gloss":"rebuke","_zh_tw_Gloss":"責備","_es_Gloss":"reprensión ","_zh_Gloss":"责备"},{"strongNumber":"G1650","matchingForm":"ἔλεγχος","stepTransliteration":"elenchos","gloss":"rebuke","_zh_tw_Gloss":"確據","_es_Gloss":"reprensión ","_zh_Gloss":"确据"},{"strongNumber":"G1951","matchingForm":"ἐπιλέγω","stepTransliteration":"epilegō","gloss":"to call/choose","_zh_tw_Gloss":"叫, 揀選了","_es_Gloss":"llamar/escoger","_zh_Gloss":"叫, 拣选了"},{"strongNumber":"G2639","matchingForm":"καταλέγω","stepTransliteration":"katalegō","gloss":"to enrol","_zh_tw_Gloss":"記在冊上","_es_Gloss":"incluir en una lista","_zh_Gloss":"记在册上"},{"strongNumber":"G3004G","matchingForm":"λέγω","stepTransliteration":"legō","gloss":"to speak","_zh_tw_Gloss":"說","_es_Gloss":"decir","_zh_Gloss":"说"},{"strongNumber":"G3004H","matchingForm":"λέγω","stepTransliteration":"legō","gloss":"to speak: call","_zh_tw_Gloss":"說","_es_Gloss":"decir","_zh_Gloss":"说"},{"strongNumber":"G4302","matchingForm":"προλέγω","stepTransliteration":"prolegō","gloss":"to foretell","_zh_tw_Gloss":"預先告訴","_es_Gloss":"p